      "body": "Constructing a transaction with 150k inputs and 150k outputs is likely to be significantly heavier than “~27 MB allocation” due to per-input/output object overhead, which can slow CI and increase peak memory usage (especially under sanitizers). Consider generating the required weight using a much smaller number of inputs/outputs (e.g., 1 in / 1 out) and inflating the serialized size via large scripts or data fields, so the test still reaches the >INT_MAX threshold while minimizing vector/object overhead and runtime.",
